# Day 22 - Longest Arithmetic Subsequence of Given Difference (Dynamic Programming)

## Problem

**LeetCode 1218 - Longest Arithmetic Subsequence of Given Difference**

Given an integer array `arr` and an integer `difference`, return the length of the longest subsequence in `arr` such that the difference between adjacent elements equals `difference`.

---

## Approaches Covered

1. Recursion
2. Memoization
3. Dynamic Programming (HashMap)

---

## Algorithm

For every element `arr[i]`:

- Find whether `arr[i] - difference` already exists in a subsequence.
- Extend that subsequence by including `arr[i]`.
- Store the best answer ending at `arr[i]`.

Transition:

dp[arr[i]] = dp[arr[i] - difference] + 1

---

## Complexity

| Approach | Time | Space |
|----------|------|-------|
| Recursion | O(2ⁿ) | O(n) |
| Memoization | O(n²) | O(n²) |
| DP (HashMap) | O(n) | O(n) |

